Study Title: Gemcitabine/Oxaliplatin (GEMOX) With or Without Erlotinib (Tarceva) in Advanced Biliary Tract Carcinoma
Brief Summary: The purpose of this study is to determine whether Gemcitabine/Oxaliplatin (GEMOX) with or without Erlotinib (Tarceva) is effective in the treatment of unresectable, metastatic biliary tract carcinoma.
Secondary Outcome Measures: Safety profile, 24 months|Response rate, 24 months|Duration of response, 24 months|Time to progression, 24 months|Overall survival, 24 months|Correlative analyses: EGFR mutation, EGFR amplification, akt expression, EGFR polymorphism analyses, 24 months
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: NONE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
Locations: Samsung Medical Center, Seoul, Korea, Republic of
